  "signature": "ed25519:b2e4f6a8c0d2e4f6a8c0d2e4f6a8c0d2e4f6a8c0d2e4f6a8c0d2e4f6a8c0d2",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/sqa-mrl2",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used under a documented SQA plan conforming to ASME V&V 10 and 21 CFR Part 11. Software version control, regression test suite (>200 benchmark cases), and change-control procedures are in place. Independent code review completed. SQA documentation archived in QMS ref. SQA-2022-047."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/ncv-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed via method of manufactured solutions (MMS) for the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver and the power-law hemolysis transport equation. Second-order spatial convergence confirmed on three systematically refined Cartesian grids. Results documented in NCV-RPT-2022-003."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/disc-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Grid convergence index (GCI) study performed on three polyhedral meshes (3.2 M, 9.7 M, 28.1 M cells). GCI for normalized hemolysis index < 1.8% on the fine grid. Richardson extrapolation applied; observed order of convergence p = 1.94. Temporal discretization: fixed time-step Δt = 5×10⁻⁵ s; Courant number < 0.8 throughout. Discretization error report DE-RPT-2023-011."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/test-cond-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Bench experiments conducted at 37 °C ± 0.5 °C with bovine blood (hematocrit 33 ± 2%). Flow rates measured by Coriolis meter (±0.15% full-scale). Rotational speed controlled by servo drive (±5 rpm). Five operating points (2–6 L/min at 2000–3500 rpm) match CFD boundary conditions. Environmental and fluid characterisation logs archived in TC-LOG-2023-009."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/output-comp-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) predicted by CFD compared against bench measurements at all 5 operating points. Mean absolute percentage error = 7.3%; maximum deviation 11.2% at highest shear operating point. Comparison accounts for experimental uncertainty (±6% NIH). Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 confirmed at all points. Detailed comparison in OC-RPT-2023-015."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH). Both are directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device) and are the quantities measured in bench testing. Clinical relevance of NIH as a hemolysis surrogate is established in ISO 10993-4 and FDA guidance. QoI mapping documented in QOI-MAP-2023-002."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/val-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry and blood analogue as the COU device. Operating envelope of validation experiments (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 rpm) encompasses the full COU operating range. Fluid properties, boundary conditions, and turbulence model (SST k-ω) are identical between validation and production runs. Relevance assessment in VAL-REL-2023-007."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/nse-scopeout",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, separate quantification of iterative solver residual error beyond standard convergence criteria is not required. Residuals converged to < 10⁻⁵ for all equations in all production runs; mass imbalance < 0.01%. This level of solver monitoring is consistent with MRL 2 requirements and is documented in NSE-SCOPE-2023-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/use-error-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Formal use-error analysis beyond standard simulation review procedures is scoped out at MRL 2. All simulation setups are peer-reviewed by a second qualified CFD engineer before execution. Setup checklists and independent review records are maintained in QMS ref. UE-SCOPE-2023-002."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/model-form-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Formal model form uncertainty quantification is scoped out at MRL 2. The SST k-ω turbulence model and Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model are established for blood pump CFD per published literature (Hariharan et al. 2011, ASME J. Biomech. Eng.). Model form scope-out documented in MF-SCOPE-2023-003."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/model-inputs-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Probabilistic sensitivity analysis of model input parameters is scoped out at MRL 2. Nominal input values (viscosity, density, hemolysis model constants) are taken from peer-reviewed sources. A deterministic sensitivity check on ±10% variation in hemolysis model constants showed < 5% change in NIH. Scope-out documented in MI-SCOPE-2023-004."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/test-samples-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Statistical characterisation of test sample variability beyond standard lot-to-lot documentation is scoped out at MRL 2. Three blood lots used in bench testing; hematocrit and viscosity measured per lot. Lot variability < 4% NIH. Scope-out documented in TS-SCOPE-2023-005."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/eip-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency analysis between validation experiment inputs and COU inputs is scoped out at MRL 2. Qualitative mapping confirms geometry, fluid properties, and boundary conditions are directly representative. Differences (bovine vs. human blood) are acknowledged and bounded by the ±10% NIH uncertainty envelope. Scope-out documented in EIP-SCOPE-2023-006."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cpb-mrl2-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/uofa-cfd-lab",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for the CFD hemolysis prediction model under CPB COU1 is accepted at Medium assurance / MRL 2. All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels: discretization error exceeds requirements (achievedLevel 3 vs. required 2) providing additional confidence in numerical accuracy. Six factors are appropriately scoped out with documented justification consistent with MRL 2 expectations. Validation evidence demonstrates CFD-predicted NIH agrees with bench measurements within combined experimental and simulation uncertainty across all five COU operating points. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 is confirmed at all points, satisfying the regulatory acceptance criterion. The provenance chain from raw experimental data through uncertainty quantification to validation results is complete and traceable. No weakeners were identified during structured review. The assessment team concludes that the model is fit for the stated purpose of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
